push , pop , slice shift ,unshift  while accessing element 
Method	Action	Changes Original?
push	add at end	✅ Yes
pop	remove from end	✅ Yes
shift	remove from start	✅ Yes
unshift	add at start	✅ Yes
slice	copy portion	❌ No


let arr = [1, 2, 3];
arr.push(4);
console.log(arr); // [1, 2, 3, 4]
Adds element to end
👉 Changes original array ✅
2. pop() → remove from END
let arr = [1, 2, 3];
arr.pop();
console.log(arr); // [1, 2]
👉 Removes last element
👉 Returns removed value
👉 Changes original array ✅
3. shift() → remove from START
let arr = [1, 2, 3];
arr.shift();
console.log(arr); // [2, 3]
👉 Removes first element
👉 Changes original array ✅
4. unshift() → add at START
let arr = [2, 3];
arr.unshift(1);
console.log(arr); // [1, 2, 3]
👉 Adds element at beginning
👉 Changes original array ✅
5. slice() → copy part (NO change)
let arr = [1, 2, 3, 4];
let newArr = arr.slice(1, 3);
console.log(newArr); // [2, 3]
console.log(arr);    // [1, 2, 3, 4]
👉 Extracts part of array
👉 Does NOT change original ❌

